OOC (OUT-OF-CHARACTER SPEECH)

Syntax: ooc <message>

Speaks out-of-character to everyone in your current room -- the same
reach as say. Unlike say, ooc skips the language system entirely, so
everyone in the room understands it regardless of active language, and
your message is tagged (ooc) so it reads as out-of-character rather
than in-fiction speech.

Use OOC for:
  - Questions about game mechanics
  - Asking for help finding something
  - Casual conversation with people in your room
  - Reporting bugs or issues to staff

Do NOT use OOC for:
  - In-character roleplay (use 'say', 'tell', or 'shout' instead)
  - Harassment or abuse

There is no global OOC channel. OOC is heard only by others physically
in your room. To reach players elsewhere, use tell (private,
one-to-one) or a carried radio tuned to a shared frequency.

See also: say, tell, shout, radio
